A simple ruby library for controlling the windows console.

Place win32console.rb either into your ruby library directory
or in the same directory as your project

Sample Code:
require 'Win32Console.rb'

# init the screen
$console = Win32Console.new;

# clear the screen
$console.clear

# change the color
$console.setColor("black","white")

# move to 5,5
$console.setPosition(5,5)

print "Hello there"

# reset the color to default
$console.setColor



